<Link id="l00387" /><CodeLine lineNumber="387"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The following structs are used for the hierarchical decode table.  After</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00388" /><CodeLine lineNumber="388"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// determining the instruction&#39;s class (i.e., which IC&#95;&#42; constant applies to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="389"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// it), the decoder reads the opcode.  Some instructions require specific</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="390"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// values of the ModR/M byte, so the ModR/M byte indexes into the final table.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="391"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="392"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// If a ModR/M byte is not required, &quot;required&quot; is left unset, and the values</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="393"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// for each instructionID are identical.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="394" lineLink="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/x86disassembler/#a48739e7e428e4607c5699d7417498956"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">typedef</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> uint16&#95;t <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/x86disassembler/#a48739e7e428e4607c5699d7417498956">InstrUID</a>;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="395"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="396"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ModRMDecisionType - describes the type of ModR/M decision, allowing the</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="397"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// consumer to determine the number of entries in it.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="398"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="399"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MODRM&#95;ONEENTRY - No matter what the value of the ModR/M byte is, the decoded</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="400"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  instruction is the same.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="401"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MODRM&#95;SPLITRM  - If the ModR/M byte is between 0 and 0xbf, the opcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="402"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  corresponds to one instruction; otherwise, it corresponds to</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="403"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  a different instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="404"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MODRM&#95;SPLITMISC- If the ModR/M byte is between 0 and 0xbf, ModR/M byte</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="405"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  divided by 8 is used to select instruction; otherwise, each</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="406"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  value of the ModR/M byte could correspond to a different</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="407"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="408"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MODRM&#95;SPLITREG - ModR/M byte divided by 8 is used to select instruction. This</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="409"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  corresponds to instructions that use reg field as opcode</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="410"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// MODRM&#95;FULL     - Potentially, each value of the ModR/M byte could correspond</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="411"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//                  to a different instruction.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="412" lineLink="#a5406c5ad64936fc7e044d3dbbeeea377"><span class="doxyHighlightPreprocessor">#define MODRMTYPES                                                             \\</span></CodeLine>
